The problem studied in the paper involves finding a minimum-cost subgraph in a given graph, which is a classic optimization problem in computer science. The problem is also related to network design and optimization, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The use of planar graphs and the relaxation technique used in the paper suggest that the problem may also be related to computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also mentions the problem being max SNP-hard and strongly NP-hard, indicating that it may be related to complexity theory (cs.CC) or discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the problem involves connectivity and paths, which suggests that it may be related to graph theory (cs.GT).
